IMPORTANT — you can pull MORE rows than the sample. These datasets are large and only a sample is shown. If the rows you need (a pre-aggregated total / all-categories / national-level row, a specific state/city, a specific year, or simply more rows) are NOT in the sample above, do NOT guess and do NOT claim the data is missing — request them. Use the listed dimension values to choose valid filters. When prompted, reply with ONLY this JSON:
{"fetch_rows":{"dataset":<dataset id>,"where":{"<column>":"<value>"},"more":false,"reason":"why you need them"}}
Provide "where" to filter rows by matching column values (case-insensitive substring), or omit "where" and set "more":true for the next batch of unseen rows. You may fetch up to {{max_drill_iters}} times.
